Early Voting Polling Places and Absentee Ballot Dropboxes



Georgias 2020 primaries have been moved to June 9. Voters can still vote in person on Election Day or vote early May 18-June 5. Early voting locations for your county can be found below. To vote in person on Election Day, you must go to your assigned polling location. That location can be found at the Secretary of State site here.

Additionally, all voters are able to request an absentee ballot, which must be turned in either via mail or dropbox before 7pm on Election Day. A request for a ballot can be found here and returned via email or via dropbox. Dropbox locations can be found below.

Have additional questions about voting in Georgia? Check out the Go Vote Georgia page here.


Instructions:

  • Click on the icon in the upper right of the map to zoom to your location
  • Use the check boxes in the upper right of the map to select/deselect Early Voting Polling Places or Absentee Ballot Dropbox locations
    • Some locations have early voting and dropboxes - check/uncheck boxes to see
  • Left click and drag to move around the map
  • Use the (+/-) in the upper right of the map or the mouse wheel to zoom in and out
  • Hover cursor over marker to see address
  • Markers are approximate locations

Source: Early Voting and Absentee Ballot Dropbox addresses compiled by The New Georgia Project
